text: The Northern Victoria Region is an electoral region of the Victorian Legislative Council, the upper house of the Victorian Parliament. It is in the northern part of Victoria. The region includes the Legislative Assembly (lower house) electoral districts of Benambra, Bendigo East, Bendigo West, Eildon, Euroa, Macedon, Mildura, Murray Plains, Ovens Valley, Shepparton and Yan Yean. ==Election results== ==References== Category:Electoral regions of Victoria Category:2006 establishments in Australia
title: Northern Victoria Region
